HEADWORD: Homobasidiomycetes
<hw>Homobasidiomycetes</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A category used in some
classification systems for various basidiomycetous fungi including e.g.
mushrooms and puffballs which are usually placed in the classes
<class>Gasteromycetes</class> and
<class>Hymenomycetes</class>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> subclass Homobasidiomycetes.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homocategoric</ent>⟦br⟧
